64
00:06:44,653 --> 00:06:46,780
What is that?

65
00:06:50,284 --> 00:06:51,576
Excuse me.

66
00:06:51,660 --> 00:06:53,620
It's a tape.

67
00:06:53,704 --> 00:06:56,623
-Where did you find it?
-It was in my pocket.

68
00:07:04,923 --> 00:07:06,967
<i>It says, "Play me. "</i>

69
00:07:38,457 --> 00:07:40,500
Come on. Come on.

70
00:07:43,378 --> 00:07:45,130
<i>Throw it over here.</i>

71
00:07:52,512 --> 00:07:54,264
Fuck.

72
00:08:05,650 --> 00:08:06,943
No?

73
00:08:32,886 --> 00:08:36,473
-Use your shirt.
-What?

74
00:08:36,556 --> 00:08:38,600
<i>Your shirt.</i>

75
00:08:52,447 --> 00:08:54,449
<i>Come on.</i>

76
00:08:59,579 --> 00:09:01,581
-It won't work.
-Look around.

77
00:09:01,665 --> 00:09:03,708
There must be something else you can use.

78
00:09:03,792 --> 00:09:07,546
-There's nothing.
-Well, there must be something.

79
00:09:20,559 --> 00:09:22,602
<i>Come on. You can do it.</i>

80
00:09:27,315 --> 00:09:28,608
Come on. Come on.

81
00:09:28,692 --> 00:09:29,985
<i>Again.</i>

82
00:09:52,757 --> 00:09:55,051
<i>Rise and shine, Adam.</i>

83
00:09:55,135 --> 00:09:57,596
<i>You're probably wondering where you are.</i>

84
00:09:57,679 --> 00:10:00,181
<i>I'll tell you where you might be.</i>

85
00:10:00,265 --> 00:10:03,143
<i>You might be in the room that you die in.</i>

86
00:10:03,226 --> 00:10:09,149
<i>Up until now, you've simply sat in the shadows,
watching others live out their lives.</i>

87
00:10:09,232 --> 00:10:13,528
<i>But what do voyeurs see
when they look into the mirror?</i>

88
00:10:13,611 --> 00:10:19,242
<i>Now, I see you as a strange mix
of someone angry yet apathetic.</i>

89
00:10:19,326 --> 00:10:21,328
<i>But mostly just pathetic.</i>

90
00:10:21,411 --> 00:10:24,581
<i>So, are you going to watch
yourself die today, Adam,</i>

91
00:10:24,664 --> 00:10:26,708
<i>or do something about it?</i>

92
00:10:28,168 --> 00:10:30,211
I don't get it.

93
00:10:31,087 --> 00:10:32,339
Throw me the player.

94
00:10:34,674 --> 00:10:37,552
No. You throw me your tape.

95
00:10:38,887 --> 00:10:42,682
Look, we're gonna have to work together,
if we want to get out of here.

96
00:10:42,766 --> 00:10:45,226
<i>-Throw it to me.
-I'm not gonna risk breaking it.</i>

97
00:10:45,310 --> 00:10:47,354
<i>You throw me your tape.</i>

98
00:11:04,245 --> 00:11:06,247
<i>Dr. Gordon...</i>

99
00:11:06,331 --> 00:11:08,833
<i>this is your wake-up call.</i>

100
00:11:08,917 --> 00:11:12,754
<i>Every day of your working life,
you have given people the news</i>

101
00:11:12,837 --> 00:11:15,215
<i>that they're gonna die soon.</i>

102
00:11:15,298 --> 00:11:19,135
<i>Now you will be the cause of death.</i>

103
00:11:19,219 --> 00:11:23,139
<i>Your aim in this game is to kill Adam.</i>

104
00:11:23,223 --> 00:11:25,308
<i>You have until 6 on the clock to do it.</i>

105
00:11:26,601 --> 00:11:29,187
<i>There's a man in the room with you.</i>

106
00:11:29,270 --> 00:11:31,856
<i>When there's that much poison in your blood,</i>

107
00:11:31,940 --> 00:11:35,527
<i>the only thing left to do is shoot yourself.</i>

108
00:11:41,574 --> 00:11:45,954
<i>There are ways to win this,
hidden all around you.</i>

109
00:11:46,037 --> 00:11:51,376
<i>Just remember,
X marks the spot for the treasure.</i>

110
00:11:51,459 --> 00:11:54,337
<i>If you do not kill Adam by six,</i>

111
00:11:55,713 --> 00:11:59,217
<i>then Alison and Diana will die,
Dr. Gordon.</i>

112
00:12:00,301 --> 00:12:03,638
<i>And I'll leave you in
this room to rot.</i>

113
00:12:04,931 --> 00:12:06,975
<i>Let the game begin.</i>

114
00:12:16,442 --> 00:12:18,444
Give me that.

115
00:12:18,528 --> 00:12:19,654
Now.

116
00:12:28,663 --> 00:12:32,083
<i>Then Alison and Diana will die,
Dr. Gordon...</i>

117
00:12:33,209 --> 00:12:36,045
<i>...and I'll leave you in
this room to rot.</i>

118
00:12:36,129 --> 00:12:41,301
<i>-Any idea who that is?
-Let the game begin.</i>

119
00:12:41,384 --> 00:12:45,054
-He knows us.
-Wait a minute.

120
00:12:45,138 --> 00:12:48,224
What do you think? Probably a joke, right?

121
00:12:48,308 --> 00:12:49,809
Shh!

122
00:12:49,892 --> 00:12:53,146
<i>-Let the game begin.
-Listen. Listen.</i>

123
00:12:54,230 --> 00:12:56,232
<i>Follow your heart.</i>

124
00:13:03,990 --> 00:13:06,242
<i>What the hell does "follow your heart" mean?</i>

125
00:13:12,832 --> 00:13:16,044
There, right next to you, on the toilet.

126
00:13:25,637 --> 00:13:28,640
Come on. Come on.

127
00:13:32,310 --> 00:13:34,354
Oh, man!

128
00:13:42,236 --> 00:13:44,989
-Anything?
-No solids.

129
00:13:45,073 --> 00:13:46,407
Take off the lid.

130
00:13:48,951 --> 00:13:50,578
<i>Come on.</i>

131
00:14:00,463 --> 00:14:02,715
I really wish I had've checked in there first.

132
00:14:02,799 --> 00:14:04,967
Huh! What is it?

133
00:14:33,871 --> 00:14:35,123
Hey.

134
00:14:36,749 --> 00:14:38,209
Mind passing me the other one?

135
00:15:05,278 --> 00:15:07,321
Fuck! Fuck!

136
00:15:50,781 --> 00:15:53,367
He doesn't want us to cut through our chains.

137
00:15:55,202 --> 00:15:57,246
He wants us to cut through our feet.

138
00:16:01,250 --> 00:16:03,461
I think I may know who's done this to us.

139
00:16:03,544 --> 00:16:05,963
What did you say?

140
00:16:06,047 --> 00:16:08,090
Well, it's not someone I know personally.

141
00:16:09,008 --> 00:16:10,635
It's just someone I know of.

142
00:16:11,719 --> 00:16:14,180
<i>Jesus Christ! Tell me. Who is it?</i>

143
00:16:16,641 --> 00:16:18,684
Last I heard...

144
00:16:19,894 --> 00:16:22,563
.. the police still hadn't caught him.

145
00:16:22,647 --> 00:16:24,982
<i>And the only reason I know that...</i>

146
00:16:25,066 --> 00:16:27,109
<i>is because I was a suspect.</i>

147
00:16:29,528 --> 00:16:31,572
<i>I'll start from the beginning.</i>

148
00:16:38,788 --> 00:16:42,833
This one's not fresh any more.
At least three weeks out.

149
00:16:42,917 --> 00:16:46,170
<i>Victim's a 46-year-old male.</i>

150
00:16:47,713 --> 00:16:52,385
<i>Died of massive blood loss,
mostly through the femoral artery.</i>

151
00:16:55,930 --> 00:16:59,517
He started at the back and tunneled
through that razor wire so fast,

152
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:01,644
it's amazing he got as far as he did.

153
00:17:03,813 --> 00:17:07,858
<i>Cut himself so deep,
we found traces of stomach acid on the floor.</i>

154
00:17:12,696 --> 00:17:14,407
We also found this.

155
00:17:17,827 --> 00:17:23,207
<i>Hello, Paul. You are a
perfectly healthy, sane, middle-class male,</i>

156
00:17:23,290 --> 00:17:24,625
<i>yet last month,</i>

157
00:17:24,708 --> 00:17:27,378
<i>you ran a straight razor across your wrists.</i>

158
00:17:29,171 --> 00:17:32,258
<i>Did you cut yourself
because you truly wanted to die,</i>

159
00:17:32,341 --> 00:17:34,969
<i>or did you just want some attention?</i>

160
00:17:35,052 --> 00:17:37,596
<i>Tonight, you'll show me.</i>

161
00:17:37,680 --> 00:17:40,641
<i>The irony is that if you want to die,</i>

162
00:17:40,724 --> 00:17:43,144
<i>you just have to stay where you are.</i>

163
00:17:43,227 --> 00:17:45,813
<i>If you want to live,
you'll have to cut yourself again.</i>

164
00:17:45,896 --> 00:17:49,066
<i>Find a path through the razor wire to the door.</i>

165
00:17:49,150 --> 00:17:50,484
<i>But hurry.</i>

166
00:17:51,652 --> 00:17:54,572
<i>At three o'clock that door will lock.</i>

167
00:17:54,655 --> 00:17:57,158
<i>And then this room becomes your tomb.</i>

168
00:17:57,241 --> 00:18:00,578
<i>How much blood will you shed
to stay alive, Paul?</i>

169
00:18:04,165 --> 00:18:07,585
Door was on a timer.
It was unlocked until three o'clock.

170
00:18:09,003 --> 00:18:12,464
Then it slammed shut. He was given two hours.

171
00:18:14,925 --> 00:18:17,052
You sick fuck!

172
00:18:22,850 --> 00:18:24,560
<i>A jigsaw piece.</i>

173
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:32,276
I think we're gonna be here for a while, Sing.

174
00:18:32,359 --> 00:18:36,071
<i>The newspapers started
calling him "the jigsaw killer".</i>

175
00:18:36,155 --> 00:18:39,491
Actually, technically speaking,

176
00:18:39,575 --> 00:18:43,120
he's... not really a murderer.

177
00:18:44,788 --> 00:18:46,707
He never killed anyone.

178
00:18:46,790 --> 00:18:49,835
<i>He finds ways for his victims
to kill themselves.</i>

179
00:18:52,546 --> 00:18:55,716
<i>Hello, Mark. If you're so sick,</i>

180
00:18:55,799 --> 00:18:59,011
<i>then why do I have so many photos of you
up and about?</i>

181
00:18:59,678 --> 00:19:02,973
<i>Let's put your so-called illness to the test.</i>

182
00:19:04,308 --> 00:19:08,187
<i>Right now, there's a slow-acting
poison in your veins.</i>

183
00:19:08,270 --> 00:19:11,273
<i>The antidote is inside the safe.</i>

184
00:19:11,357 --> 00:19:12,399
Help!

185
00:19:13,484 --> 00:19:17,613
<i>The combination to the safe...
is written on the wall.</i>

186
00:19:17,696 --> 00:19:19,782
<i>Hurry up and program it in.</i>

187
00:19:19,865 --> 00:19:21,992
<i>But watch your step.</i>

188
00:19:22,076 --> 00:19:27,331
<i>By the way, that's a flammable substance
smeared on your body.</i>

189
00:19:27,414 --> 00:19:30,626
<i>So, I would be careful
with that candle, if I were you.</i>

190
00:19:30,709 --> 00:19:36,465
<i>Or all the people you've burned with your act
just might have their revenge.</i>

191
00:19:40,969 --> 00:19:42,179
Aaaargh!

192
00:19:43,514 --> 00:19:44,890
I found something else.

193
00:19:46,016 --> 00:19:48,018
Well, two things, actually.

194
00:19:48,102 --> 00:19:51,355
There was someone standing outside,
watching through this hole.

195
00:19:51,438 --> 00:19:56,276
Our friend Jigsaw likes to book himself
front-row seats to his own sick little games.

196
00:19:56,360 --> 00:19:58,654
<i>He was there at the last one as well.</i>

197
00:19:59,780 --> 00:20:03,117
Only, this time... he left us his penlight.

198
00:20:07,037 --> 00:20:08,580
Hm...

199
00:20:09,665 --> 00:20:11,667
Get a rush on the prints.

200
00:20:11,750 --> 00:20:14,128
Copy that.

201
00:20:14,211 --> 00:20:18,215
This patient has an inoperable frontal lobe
tumor extending across the midline.

202
00:20:18,298 --> 00:20:21,135
It started as colon cancer.

203
00:20:21,218 --> 00:20:24,471
The patient has come in for a standard checkup,

204
00:20:24,555 --> 00:20:28,183
by which we can monitor the rate
at which his condition is declining.

205
00:20:28,267 --> 00:20:30,686
-The patient had...
-His name is John.

206
00:20:31,895 --> 00:20:35,065
Dr. Gordon. He's a very interesting person.

207
00:20:37,776 --> 00:20:39,778
Thank you for that information, Zep.

208
00:20:39,862 --> 00:20:43,824
<i>As you can see, our orderlies
form very special bonds with the patients.</i>

209
00:20:45,159 --> 00:20:47,202
<i>Continuing on, the patient had...</i>

210
00:20:47,286 --> 00:20:50,122
<i>Dr. Gordon, please page the operator.</i>

211
00:20:51,665 --> 00:20:56,170
Someone doesn't want me to tell you
what the patient had! Excuse me.

212
00:21:00,924 --> 00:21:02,217
Dr. Gordon.

213
00:21:03,343 --> 00:21:06,555
I'm Detective Tapp, this is Detective Sing.
City homicide.

214
00:21:06,638 --> 00:21:11,351
-Very impressive.
-Oh, thank you.

215
00:21:11,435 --> 00:21:13,187
I do my best.

216
00:21:15,939 --> 00:21:18,317
<i>-Sorry to interrupt you while you work.
-Fine.</i>

217
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:20,444
Now, how can I help you gentlemen?

218
00:21:20,527 --> 00:21:26,408
Are you able to tell us where you were
between the hours of 11 PM and 1 AM last night?

219
00:21:26,491 --> 00:21:29,369
Why is it that you're interested?

220
00:21:29,453 --> 00:21:31,872
We'd like to ask a few questions about it.

221
00:21:31,955 --> 00:21:36,627
For your sake, I think it's best
if we do it down at the station.

222
00:21:36,710 --> 00:21:41,340
-Would you like to follow us there?
-I'm afraid that's out of the question.

223
00:21:41,423 --> 00:21:45,719
I can't just leave, I have work to do.
Plus my wife has the car today.

224
00:21:45,802 --> 00:21:48,138
That's OK. You can ride with us.

225
00:21:48,222 --> 00:21:49,556
Doc?

226
00:21:53,560 --> 00:21:56,188
I'm sorry.

227
00:21:56,271 --> 00:21:59,942
You'll have to tell me again.
What is this all about?

228
00:22:01,068 --> 00:22:03,111
Is this yours, Doctor?

229
00:22:15,749 --> 00:22:19,294
<i>So you have no idea how your penlight
showed up at the murder scene?</i>

230
00:22:19,378 --> 00:22:21,421
Of course not, Brett.

231
00:22:24,841 --> 00:22:28,095
<i>Well, I have to ask.
What were you doing last night?</i>

232
00:22:31,014 --> 00:22:33,058
I was seeing someone.

233
00:22:34,685 --> 00:22:36,061
Who?

234
00:22:39,731 --> 00:22:42,109
Look, if you can't be honest with me...

235
00:22:42,192 --> 00:22:44,236
I was visiting someone, It wasn't a patient.

236
00:22:44,319 --> 00:22:46,196
<i>All right?</i>

237
00:22:48,615 --> 00:22:50,617
What am I gonna do?

238
00:22:50,701 --> 00:22:53,286
Well, as your lawyer and your friend,

239
00:22:53,370 --> 00:22:58,667
my advice to you is to bite the bullet
